Key Match Events: Ben Stokes scored an unbeaten 122 off 94 balls
Chris Woakes took 4 wickets for 21 runs
Rashid has his third wicket, Moeen Ali strikes for the second time, and Scott Edwards departs after scoring 38 runs
Pre-Game Insights: England have won only one game in seven games so far in the ongoing tournament
Jos Buttler and Co. suffered five consecutive defeats
England's last defeat came against Australia at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad
Netherlands have won two and lost five games in the competition
Scott Edwards-led Netherlands suffered a seven-wicket defeat over Afghanistan
Post-Match Reflections: England skipper Jos Buttler expressed his delight over the victory, saying it has been a tough World Cup for them
Buttler praised the partnership between Stokes and Woakes, saying it was fantastic
Wickets taken by England's bowlers were highlighted, with Ben Stokes being particularly mentioned for his batting
Scott Edwards, the losing skipper, acknowledged the strong performance of England's bowlers and the quality of the pitch
